main event: Two round objects were observed in the sky, one white and the other with flame, during a military sighting in October 1965.
interesting points: The first object was round and white, disappearing from sight in about 15 seconds,The second object was similar but covered with flame and disappeared in about 10 seconds,The objects were almost directly overhead and observed for approximately 4 minutes, The second object crossed the flight path of the first,The report concluded that the objects could be meteor activity.
sighted object: two round objects, one white and one covered with flame
witness description: William T Hall, MSGT, AF 17912233, First Sergeant, 4OS Combat Support Squadron
